      "scoring_520405": "Scoring Procedure and InterpretationThe Prescription Stimulant Expectancy Questionnaire (PSEQ) score is calculated by averaging the item scores. Half of the items (1, 2, 4, 5, 6, 7, 11, 13, 23, 24, 28, 30, 31, 32, 34, 35, 36, 37, 38, and 39) are scored with 0 = \"Not at all,\" 1= \"Sometimes,\" and 2 = \"Very often or always.\" The other half of the items (3, 8, 9, 10, 12, 14, 15, 16, 17, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 25, 26, 27, 29, 33, and 40) are reverse-scored with 2 = \"Not at all,\" 1 = \"Sometimes,\" and 0 = \"Very often or always.\"",
      "likert_1": "Not at all",
      "likert_2": "Sometimes",
      "likert_3": "Very often or always"
    }
  }
}
